Repository Name Unauthorized: Tudor Place Historic House and Garden
Notes: The Tudor Place archival collection of approximately 300 linear feet or 250,000 items consists of the personal papers of the Peter family from the mid-18th century to 1983. It includes correspondence, diaries, scrapbooks, financial records, inventories, blueprints, architectural drawings, and ephemera. In addition, a substantial collection of 5,000 books from the 18th through 20th centuries and mid-19th-century photographs complete this rare resource for students and scholars.
